{
    "level": "B2–C1",
    "intro": "In this topic, you will learn how <strong>style and formality</strong> influence the choice between active and passive, and when using the passive is <strong>appropriate</strong> or <strong>undesirable</strong>.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "Formal",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "The passive gives the text <strong>formality and objectivity</strong>:",
            "example": "The experiment was conducted in 2023."
        },
        {
            "label": "Scientific",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "In <strong>scientific texts</strong> the passive is the norm:",
            "example": "The data were analyzed using SPSS."
        },
        {
            "label": "Colloquial",
            "color": "amber",
            "text": "In <strong>spoken language</strong> the active sounds more natural:",
            "example": "We analyzed the data. (не: The data were analyzed by us)"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. Where the passive is typical and appropriate",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Scientific texts",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "In <strong>scientific articles</strong> and studies:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The experiment was conducted under controlled conditions.",
                    "ua": "The experiment was conducted under controlled conditions."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The samples were collected from five locations.",
                    "ua": "The samples were collected from five locations."
                },
                {
                    "en": "It was observed that temperature affects the results.",
                    "ua": "It was observed that temperature affects the results."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Official documents",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "In <strong>laws, contracts, instructions</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Smoking is prohibited in this area.",
                    "ua": "Smoking is prohibited in this area."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Applications must be submitted by Friday.",
                    "ua": "Applications must be submitted by Friday."
                },
                {
                    "en": "This contract is governed by UK law.",
                    "ua": "This contract is governed by UK law."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "News and media",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "In <strong>news messages</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The suspect was arrested yesterday.",
                    "ua": "The suspect was arrested yesterday."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The new law has been approved.",
                    "ua": "The new law has been approved."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Several people were injured in the accident.",
                    "ua": "Several people were injured in the accident."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Technical instructions",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "In <strong>technical documentation</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The device should be charged for 2 hours.",
                    "ua": "The device should be charged for 2 hours."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Cookies are used to improve user experience.",
                    "ua": "Cookies are used to improve user experience."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Updates are installed automatically.",
                    "ua": "Updates are installed automatically."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Formal vs Informal style",
    "intro": "Comparing the same message in different styles:",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "Formal: The report was submitted on time.",
            "ua": "Formal: The report was submitted on time.",
            "note": "Official document, email."
        },
        {
            "en": "Informal: I submitted the report on time.",
            "ua": "Informal: I submitted the report on time.",
            "note": "A conversation with a colleague."
        },
        {
            "en": "Formal: Mistakes were made.",
            "ua": "Formal: Mistakes were made.",
            "note": "Official statement (without specifying the culprit)."
        },
        {
            "en": "Informal: We made mistakes.",
            "ua": "Informal: We made mistakes.",
            "note": "Acknowledgment of responsibility."
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 Passive can be used to avoid responsibility or blame!"
}

{
    "title": "3. When it is better to avoid the passive",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Spoken language",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "In <strong>everyday communication</strong> the passive voice sounds unnatural:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Unnatural: The ball was kicked by John.",
                    "ua": "Unnatural: The ball was kicked by John."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Natural: John kicked the ball.",
                    "ua": "Natural: John kicked the ball."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "When the performer is important",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "If <strong>it matters who performed the action</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Awkward: The book was written by Shakespeare.",
                    "ua": "Awkward: The book was written by Shakespeare."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Better: Shakespeare wrote the book.",
                    "ua": "Better: Shakespeare wrote the book."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Excessive passive",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "Too much passive <strong>tires the reader</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Too much passive: The report was written, was reviewed, and was submitted.",
                    "ua": "Too much passive: The report was written, was reviewed, and was submitted."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Better: We wrote, reviewed, and submitted the report.",
                    "ua": "Better: We wrote, reviewed, and submitted the report."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "4. Be-passive vs Get-passive by formality",
    "intro": "The choice between <strong>be</strong> and <strong>get</strong> depends on style:",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "be + V3",
            "title": "Formal, neutral",
            "subtitle": "The document was signed. (officially)"
        },
        {
            "label": "get + V3",
            "title": "Informal, conversational",
            "subtitle": "The document got signed. (colloquial)"
        },
        {
            "label": "Scientific texts",
            "title": "Only be-passive",
            "subtitle": "The data were analyzed. ✅"
        },
        {
            "label": "Daily broadcasting",
            "title": "Get-passive is valid",
            "subtitle": "He got promoted! (positive news)"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "5. Stylistic effects of the passive",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Objectivity",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "The passive gives the impression of <strong>objectivity and impartiality</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "It is believed that climate change is accelerating.",
                    "ua": "It is believed that climate change is accelerating."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The results were verified independently.",
                    "ua": "The results were verified independently."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Depersonalization",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "The passive <strong>hides the performer</strong> (sometimes intentionally):",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Mistakes were made.",
                    "ua": "Mistakes were made."
                },
                {
                    "en": "It has been decided to close the factory.",
                    "ua": "It has been decided to close the factory."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Focus on action/object",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "The passive <strong>emphasizes the action or result</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The Mona Lisa was painted in the early 16th century.",
                    "ua": "The Mona Lisa was painted in the early 16th century."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The building was destroyed in the fire.",
                    "ua": "The building was destroyed in the fire."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "6. Academic style: recommendations",
    "intro": "Modern recommendations for the passive voice in academic texts:",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "Traditional: The results were analyzed.",
            "ua": "Traditional: The results were analyzed.",
            "note": "Still widely used."
        },
        {
            "en": "Modern: We analyzed the results.",
            "ua": "Modern: We analyzed the results.",
            "note": "Recommended by many magazines."
        },
        {
            "en": "Mixed: The samples were collected. We analyzed them.",
            "ua": "Mixed: The samples were collected. We analyzed them.",
            "note": "Balance of objectivity and clarity."
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 Check the requirements of a specific journal or institution!"
}

{
    "title": "7. Typical mistakes",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Error 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Get-passive in formal text.",
            "wrong": "The experiment got conducted.",
            "right": "✅ The experiment was conducted."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Excessive passive without need.",
            "wrong": "The ball was kicked by John to Mary.",
            "right": "✅ John kicked the ball to Mary."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Passive with an obvious doer.",
            "wrong": "I was asked a question by the teacher.",
            "right": "✅ The teacher asked me a question."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 4",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Passive in an informal context.",
            "wrong": "A good time was had by all at the party.",
            "right": "✅ Everyone had a good time at the party."
        }
    ]
}
